definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) The husk of grain ; chaff .
( slang , mildly vulgar , uncountable ) Something worthless or of poor quality; junk.
examples: The long-running game show went from offering good prizes to crap in no time.

definitions.definition: ( slang , mildly vulgar , uncountable ) Nonsense; something untrue.
examples: The college student boasted of completing a 10,000-word essay on Shakespeare, but that claim was utter crap .
I stepped in some dog crap that was on the sidewalk.

definitions.definition: ( slang , mildly vulgar , countable ) An act of defecation .
examples: I have to take a crap .
